{"word":"ἔπαλξις","slug":"ἔπαλξις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔπαλξις</b></el> <el>(ἔπαλξις, εως) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐπαλέξω'><el>ἐπαλέξω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a means of defence</i>: in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>battlements</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—in sg. <i>the battlements, parapet</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>a defence, protection</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}